If you’re integrating OnchainKit into an existing project, you can manually install it using the following steps:Install OnchainKit:bash

npm install @coinbase/onchainkit

Obtain a Client API Key: Visit the Coinbase Developer Platform to get your Client API Key and add it to a .env file in your project root:env

NEXT_PUBLIC_ONCHAINKIT_API_KEY=YOUR_CLIENT_API_KEY

Set Up Providers: Create a providers.tsx file to configure the OnchainKitProvider with your API key and desired blockchain (e.g., Base). For example:tsx

import { OnchainKitProvider } from '@coinbase/onchainkit';
import { base } from 'wagmi/chains';
import type { ReactNode } from 'react';

export function Providers({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <OnchainKitProvider apiKey={process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_ONCHAINKIT_API_KEY} chain={base}>
      {children}
    </OnchainKitProvider>
  );
}

Wrap Your App: Wrap your application with the Providers component in your root layout file (e.g., app/layout.tsx).
Add Styles: Import OnchainKit’s pre-configured styles by adding the following line to your layout file:tsx

import '@coinbase/onchainkit/styles.css';

